# State Management

## Rules
- State library: {{STATE_LIBRARY}} (pick a stable, widely-supported option).
- Separate server state from client state: {{SERVER_VS_CLIENT_STATE}}.
- Data fetching: {{DATA_FETCHING}} (e.g. react-query); handle loading/error explicitly.
- Don't put in global state something only one component uses.

## Sync with the API
- Data shapes match the backend contract; validate responses at the boundary.
